<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>“He was the most generous person in the community and he was a peacemaker,” said Zonke. She said at this stage they have not yet decided what the event will be. “We’re trying to work with his industry friends to come up with a youth programme. “Sbusiso was passionate about helping young kids and the youth. “The programme will focus on the youth in whatever field they want to pursue, and give them hope.” Bandile told the SunTeam his idea was inspired by events like the annual Brown Dash Tribute.“This is personal to me because I grew up with Mashesha and I’ve seen what he has done in the community. “It’s about time we honoured him. We’ve brought Tira and Big NUZ on board,” he said. Tira said: “I’ve been in contact with Zonke and I jumped at the opportunity. There is no way I wasn’t going to be part of it. R loved his community.”Bandile said they’re hoping to have the event on 14 April.